<div class="feed rssfeed"><h2>

 <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/RS-IAEA-offers-guidance-on-lifting-nuclear-emergencies-1603185.html">

 IAEA offers guidance on lifting nuclear emergencies

 </a>

</h2>

<p>

 <strong>Published</strong>: Fri, 16 Mar 2018 16:31:01 GMT

</p>

<p>

 
Countries have made preparations for responding to nuclear and radiological emergencies, but too little has been done to prepare for the lifting of those emergencies, according to the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA). It has now published a guide providing advice on the transition to a normal state following an emergency.


</p>

<br/><h2>

 <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/NP-IAEA-strengthens-African-sustainable-development-1603187.html">

 IAEA strengthens African sustainable development

 </a>

</h2>

<p>

 <strong>Published</strong>: Fri, 16 Mar 2018 16:17:59 GMT

</p>

<p>

 
The International Atomic Energy Agency and the African Union Commission have signed their first practical arrangements for the safe, secure and peaceful use of nuclear technologies for sustainable development in Africa. <br />


</p>

<br/><h2>

 <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/NN-Progress-in-Indonesian-SMR-project-1603184.html">

 Progress with Indonesian SMR project

 </a>

</h2>

<p>

 <strong>Published</strong>: Fri, 16 Mar 2018 16:47:05 GMT

</p>

<p>

 
<img title="RDE - 48" alt="RDE - 48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/RDE%20-%2048.jpg" align="left" />Indonesia's National Atomic Energy Agency has launched a roadmap for developing a detailed engineering design for its Experimental Power Reactor. The design of the country's indigenous small modular reactor is expected to be finalised later this year.


</p>

<br/><h2>

 <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/RS-UK-explains-enabling-regulation-approach-16021801.html">

 UK explains 'enabling regulation' approach

 </a>

</h2>

<p>

 <strong>Published</strong>: Fri, 16 Mar 2018 16:22:27 GMT

</p>

<p>

 
The UK's Office for Nuclear Regulation has published a guide on how it can work with dutyholders to improve safety and security activity in the nuclear industry. The document, <em>Holding to Account and Influencing Improvements - Enabling Regulation in Practice</em>, features a number of case studies which place enabling regulation in the context of the legal and practical obligations on ONR and industry dutyholders.


</p>

<br/><h2>

 <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/RS-NRC-issues-confirmatory-order-for-Entergy-violations-1503188.html">

 NRC issues confirmatory order for Entergy violations

 </a>

</h2>

<p>

 <strong>Published</strong>: Fri, 16 Mar 2018 14:56:26 GMT

</p>

<p>

 
<img title="Grand_Gulf_(NRC)-48" align="left" alt="Grand_Gulf_(NRC)-48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/Grand Gulf 48.jpg" />The US Nuclear Regulatory Commission has issued a confirmatory order to Entergy Nuclear Operations, Inc and Entergy Operations, Inc, documenting actions they have agreed to take to implement programmes designed to prevent wilful misconduct at their fleet of seven operating nuclear power plants. <br />


</p>

<br/><h2>

 <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/RS-Amano-commends-Pakistan-nuclear-safety-and-security-1503187.html">

 Amano commends Pakistan nuclear safety and security

 </a>

</h2>

<p>

 <strong>Published</strong>: Thu, 15 Mar 2018 14:54:42 GMT

</p>

<p>

 
<img title="Amano_Abbasi_March_2018_(PMO)-48" align="left" alt="Amano_Abbasi_March_2018_(PMO)-48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/Amano-Abbasi 48.jpg" />Pakistan is ready to strengthen its relationship with the International Atomic Energy Agency, the country's prime minister, Shahid Khaqan Abbasi, told IAEA Director General Yukiya Amano this week. Amano commended Pakistan's efforts to increase nuclear safety and security. <br />


</p>

<br/><h2>

 <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/NN-UK-firm-sees-year-end-launch-of-pulsed-power-device-15031801.html">

 UK firm sees year-end launch of pulsed power device

 </a>

</h2>

<p>

 <strong>Published</strong>: Thu, 15 Mar 2018 14:41:15 GMT

</p>

<p>

 
<img title="Machine 3 - 48" style="BORDER-TOP-COLOR: ; BORDER-LEFT-COLOR: ; BORDER-BOTTOM-COLOR: ; BORDER-RIGHT-COLOR: ; align: left" alt="Machine 3 - 48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/Machine%203%20-%2048.jpg" align="left" />First Light Fusion is investing GBP3.6 million (USD5.0 million) building what it says will be the only pulsed power machine of its scale in the world dedicated to researching fusion energy. The Oxford, England-based company said on 12 March it expects to commission the device - Machine 3 - by the end of this year.


</p>

<br/><h2>

 <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/C-Ohi-3-reaches-critical-milestone-in-restart-1503184.html">

 Ohi 3 reaches critical milestone in restart

 </a>

</h2>

<p>

 <strong>Published</strong>: Thu, 15 Mar 2018 16:43:03 GMT

</p>

<p>

 
<img title="Ohi 3 and 4 48" alt="Ohi 3 and 4 48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/Ohi%203%20and%204%2048.jpg" align="left" />Unit 3 of the Ohi nuclear power plant in Japan's Fukui Prefecture reached criticality this morning, operator Kansai Electric Power Company announced. The reactor - the sixth to be restarted after clearing the country's revised safety regulations - is expected to resume commercial operation early next month.


</p>

<br/><h2>

 <a href="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/NN-Terrestrial-signs-IMSR-fuel-testing-contract-1403185.html">

 Terrestrial signs IMSR fuel testing contract

 </a>

</h2>

<p>

 <strong>Published</strong>: Thu, 15 Mar 2018 17:46:05 GMT

</p>

<p>

 
<img title="IMSR core cutaway - 48" alt="IMSR core cutaway - 48" src="http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/uploadedImages/wnn/Images/IMSR%20core%20cutaway%20-%2048.jpg" align="left" />Terrestrial Energy of Canada has signed a contract for technical services with the European Commission's Joint Research Centre in Karlsruhe, Germany. Under the contract, JRC will perform confirmatory studies of the fuel and primary coolant salt mixture for Terrestrial's Integrated Molten Salt Reactor (IMSR).


</p>

 French-US firms create storage JV in Texas

 </a>

 <strong>Published</strong>: Wed, 14 Mar 2018 16:37:24 GMT
